title: Jenna Bush Hager & ResortPass: Redefining Self-Care & Staycations for Moms
content: Jenna Bush Hager & ResortPass: Redefining Self-Care & Staycations for Moms In an exclusive and exciting collaboration, "Today" show host Jenna Bush Hager has teamed up with ResortPass, a pioneering platform transforming how individuals, particularly busy mothers, approach self-care and leisure. This partnership marks a significant stride in encouraging much-needed breaks and accessible luxury experiences through day-long resort and spa access. This video delves into the essence of this collaboration, exploring how it aims to redefine the very concept of personal well-being in today's fast-paced world. Jenna Bush Hager, a multifaceted personality juggling her roles as a mother of three, a successful business owner, and a prominent TV star, passionately advocates for the critical importance of incorporating alone time into one's routine. She highlights a pivotal shift in societal attitudes towards mothers prioritizing their own needs, moving away from past stigmas and embracing self-care as a necessity, not a luxury. Her personal endorsement of ResortPass comes from her own positive experiences as an avid user of the platform. ResortPass offers a flexible and affordable gateway to relaxation, with services ranging from serene poolside lounging to rejuvenating massage therapies, often starting at an accessible price point of $25. This affordability and flexibility are key aspects that this partnership aims to emphasize, making premium self-care experiences attainable for a broader audience. Michael Wolf, the CEO of ResortPass, perfectly articulates why Jenna Bush Hager is the quintessential partner for their brand. He underscores her unwavering belief in the transformative power of taking breaks and her outspoken advocacy for finding balance amidst the demanding schedules of a high-profile media career, the responsibilities of motherhood, and her ventures in the publishing world. Her authenticity and genuine commitment to the message resonate deeply with ResortPass's mission to facilitate moments of tranquility and rejuvenation. A particularly innovative aspect of this collaboration involves Hager's new book imprint, Thousand Voices Publishing. As part of this unique initiative, the imprint's inaugural book, "Conform" by Ariel Sullivan, will be thoughtfully distributed to customers who book services directly through the ResortPass app. This cross-promotional strategy not only enhances the value proposition for ResortPass users but also introduces a new literary work to an engaged audience already invested in personal enrichment and relaxation. Jenna suggests that utilizing ResortPass for these delightful day vacations provides a liberating sense of "pretending you're traveling," even while remaining within the comforts of your own city. This concept beautifully intertwines with the joy of reading, creating a perfect synergy for a truly immersive and relaxing experience. The partnership also taps into a broader trend observed in the wellness industry: the exponential surge in interest surrounding spas and medi-spas, particularly in the post-pandemic era. This heightened consumer awareness and prioritization of health and well-being underscore the timeliness and relevance of the Jenna Bush Hager and ResortPass alliance. The video encapsulates how this collaboration is not just about booking a day at a resort; it‚Äôs about fostering a lifestyle where self-care is integrated, celebrated, and accessible, ultimately empowering individuals to lead more balanced and fulfilling lives. It‚Äôs a compelling narrative for anyone seeking practical ways to de-stress, recharge, and rediscover themselves amidst life‚Äôs demands. title: ‚Å†Benefits Of Castor Oil Apply Every Night Before Bed | Castor Oil For Skin | Healthy Skin Routine
content: #benefits #castors #oil Hey everyone! Today, I want to talk about something that might not be on everyone's radar but has been a game changer for me: castor oil. Yes, you heard that right‚Äîcastor oil! Now, I know what you might be thinking. ‚ÄúIsn‚Äôt that just for laxatives?‚Äù Well, yes, it has that reputation, but trust me, it‚Äôs so much more than that. If you‚Äôve been searching for a natural beauty hack, let me tell you why applying castor oil every night before bed could be one of the best decisions you make for your skin and hair. First off, let‚Äôs dive into why castor oil is such a powerhouse. It‚Äôs packed with ricinoleic acid, which is a fancy way of saying it‚Äôs super moisturizing. This means if you apply it to your skin, it can help lock in that precious hydration while you sleep. Imagine waking up with plump, dewy skin instead of that dry, tired look we all dread. I mean, who doesn‚Äôt want to wake up feeling like they just had a spa day? Now, if you‚Äôre like me and have struggled with dry patches or uneven skin tone, castor oil could be your new best friend. It has anti-inflammatory properties that can help soothe irritated skin. You know those nights when you‚Äôve had a long day, and your skin just feels like it‚Äôs been through a war? A little castor oil can work wonders, calming down redness and irritation. Plus, it‚Äôs non-comedogenic, which means it won‚Äôt clog your pores. So, if you‚Äôre worried about breakouts, fear not! Let‚Äôs not forget about its benefits for our hair. If you‚Äôve been dreaming of longer, thicker hair, castor oil might be the secret ingredient you‚Äôve been missing. I started applying it to my scalp every night, and honestly, the results have been incredible. Not only does it nourish your hair follicles, but it also promotes hair growth. I‚Äôve noticed my hair feeling stronger and looking shinier. It‚Äôs like giving your hair a little hug before bedtime. And here‚Äôs a fun fact: castor oil can also help with split ends. If you‚Äôre someone who frequently styles their hair or uses heat tools, you know how damaging that can be. A little castor oil on the ends can help seal those split ends, preventing further damage and keeping your hair looking healthy. It‚Äôs like a protective barrier, and who doesn‚Äôt want that? Now, I get it‚Äîsome of you might be skeptical about the consistency of castor oil. It‚Äôs thick, and that‚Äôs putting it lightly. But here‚Äôs a tip: a little goes a long way. You don‚Äôt need to slather it on; just a few drops will do the trick. Warm it up between your palms, and then gently massage it into your skin or hair. You‚Äôll find that it absorbs nicely, especially if you give it a little time before hitting the pillow. And let‚Äôs not overlook the relaxing ritual of applying castor oil before bed. It‚Äôs a moment of self-care, a time to unwind from the chaos of the day. As you massage it into your skin or scalp, take a deep breath and let go of the stress. It‚Äôs not just about the beauty benefits; it‚Äôs about nurturing your body and mind. So, if you haven‚Äôt already, I encourage you to give castor oil a shot. Incorporate it into your nightly routine, and watch as it transforms your skin and hair. You might just find that this humble oil becomes your go-to beauty secret. content: Join me as I take on the challenge of living my best life in Johannesburg ‚Äîlet's see how much fun we can pack into one adventure! I'm super excited to share with you my experience exploring this vibrant city, from its stunning landscapes to its rich culture and history. Over the next few minutes, you'll get to see the best of Johannesburg, and I hope you'll be as thrilled as I am to discover what this amazing city has to offer. Finding the perfect balance between adventure and relaxation in a city as dynamic as Johannesburg can be tough. There's always something new to explore, a new restaurant to try, or a new trail to hike, but it's also important to take a step back and soak it all in. For me, that balance is key to enjoying the city to the fullest. I've had my fair share of action-packed days, but also moments of tranquility that have allowed me to recharge. The challenge is real, though - with so many options, it's easy to get caught up in the hustle and bustle and forget to take time for yourself. That's why I've made it a point to prioritize self-care, whetherm that means taking a morning jog through the beautiful parks or indulging in a relaxing spa day. By finding that sweet spot, I've been able to experience the city in a way that's authentic and fulfilling. As I navigate the city, I've come to realize that it's the little things that make Johannesburg so special. From the friendly locals to the vibrant markets and cafes, there's a unique energy that's hard to find anywhere else. And, of course, having Jetour by my side has made all the difference - their support and expertise have allowed me to explore the city with confidence and freedom. Johannesburg is a city that's full of life and energy, and I feel so lucky to have had the chance to experience it. From the moment I arrived, I knew that I was in for an adventure. The city's rich history, stunning landscapes, and warm hospitality have won me over, and I'm excited to share some of my favorite moments with you. One of my standout moments was visiting the iconic Table Mountain, which offered breathtaking views of the city. I remember feeling a sense of awe as I took in the stunning panorama, feeling grateful to be living my best life in this incredible city. Another highlight was exploring the vibrant neighborhoods, each with its own unique character and charm. From the trendy boutiques to the bustling street food markets, there's always something new to discover. I also had the chance to interact with some of the friendly locals, who shared with me their stories and experiences of living in Johannesburg. It was amazing to see how passionate people are about their city, and I felt inspired by their love and enthusiasm. These interactions made me realize just how much there is to learn and discover in this city. Recapping my adventure in Johannesburg, I'm filled with so much joy and gratitude. Exploring this city with Jetour has been an absolute dream, and I feel like I've only scratched the surface of what it has to offer. The beauty, excitement, and warmth of Johannesburg have captured my heart, and I know that I'll be back soon. If you've had your own adventures in Johannesburg, I'd love to hear about them in the comments below. Let's share our experiences and inspire each other to explore this amazing city. And if you're interested in more travel videos like this, be sure to check out my channel for more exciting content.

Techniques for Mindful Self-Indulgence Practice Moderation Enjoy your favorite indulgences in moderation to avoid negative consequences and maintain balance. Strategies to Avoid Overindulgence Create a Schedule: Plan your indulgences to prevent spontaneous overindulgence. title: Hey there, busy bees! üêù
content: Hey there, busy bees! üêù I know how hectic the week can get, so here's a little guide to help you chill out and recharge over the weekend: 1. **Disconnect**: Turn off those email notifications and give yourself a tech break. Your brain will thank you! What are your favorite ways to unplug from technology? 2. **Move It**: Whether it's yoga, a hike, or just a walk in the park, getting active helps clear your mind. Do you have any favorite spots for outdoor activities? 3. **Eat Well**: Prep some healthy meals in advance. Think simple salads, smoothies, and one-pot wonders that save time but keep you energized. Got any go-to recipes you love? 4. **Pamper Time**: Treat yourself to a spa day at home. A long bath, some candles, and good music can work wonders. What's your ultimate self-care ritual? 5. **Plan Ahead**: Spend a little time planning out your week. It can help reduce stress and keep you focused. How do you stay organized for the week ahead? 6. **Connect**: Catch up with friends or family. Human connection is key to mental wellness. Any fun plans with loved ones this weekend? Ladies, remember to take care of yourselves too! Practice self-care, #love , set boundaries, and don't be afraid to ask for help when you need it. How do you ensure you‚Äôre setting enough boundaries to maintain your mental wellness? Enjoy your weekend and get ready to crush it next week! üí™‚ú® #valuedhr #businessowners #success #virtualassistants #instagood #follow #life

title: Hey there, busy bees! üêù
content: Hey there, busy bees! üêù I know how hectic the week can get, so here's a little guide to help you chill out and recharge over the weekend: 1. **Disconnect**: Turn off those email notifications and give yourself a tech break. Your brain will thank you! What are your favorite ways to unplug from technology? 2. **Move It**: Whether it's yoga, a hike, or just a walk in the park, getting active helps clear your mind. Do you have any favorite spots for outdoor activities? 3. **Eat Well**: Prep some healthy meals in advance. Think simple salads, smoothies, and one-pot wonders that save time but keep you energized. Got any go-to recipes you love? 4. **Pamper Time**: Treat yourself to a spa day at home. A long bath, some candles, and good music can work wonders. What's your ultimate self-care ritual? 5. **Plan Ahead**: Spend a little time planning out your week. It can help reduce stress and keep you focused. How do you stay organized for the week ahead? 6. **Connect**: Catch up with friends or family. Human connection is key to mental wellness. Any fun plans with loved ones this weekend? Ladies, remember to take care of yourselves too! Practice self-care, #love , set boundaries, and don't be afraid to ask for help when you need it. How do you ensure you‚Äôre setting enough boundaries to maintain your mental wellness? Enjoy your weekend and get ready to crush it next week! üí™‚ú® #valuedhr #businessowners #success #virtualassistants #instagood #follow #life

title: Everyday is a Spa Day with Jennifer Olley
content: After being diagnosed with an acute auto immune illness that left her body unable to create energy to do any daily activities, Jennifer Olley was left to find a way to heal herself as the medical community said there was no cure. Starting with a book from a Wales physician, she changed her diet, then quickly realized the key to wellness is through regulating the nervous system. In this episode, Jennifer explains how our bodies know how to heal itself and we all need to take self care seriously as it is not a luxury, it is a necessity. Everyday is a spa day, was her mantra that got her through healing herself. We need to regulate our nervous system so our immune system can turn on and the body can heal itself. Examples of ways to regulate the nervous system mentioned in this episode: -Qi Gong -Meditation -Laying Still -Breathwork -Cold Immersion -Box Breathing -Wim Hof app or other breathwork apps Jennifer uses the analogy of a traffic light to ask yourself, What does my Heart, Mind and Body say about this? Red is stop, Green is go. All areas need to work together. Listen to them. Jennifer Olley is a clinical social worker with 25 years of experience, specializing in supporting individuals with traumatic histories, including those in psychiatric and spiritual crisis. She owns and operates Self-Integrated: Aligning Your Body, Mind, and Spirit, offering a holistic integrative approach by recognizing that true alignment requires balance across all aspects of the self. Thats new to me...but those are low priority, and im sure she deserves a full spa day from time to time. But I do have to object, my ex was useless at home, totally no help, when i worked, she did nothing, when i was a stay at home day, easiest job i ever had by the way, she did LESS than nothing, she found ways to deliberately make things hard because didnt understand how easy it was for me to still do more than she did when I worked, so when i didnt work, she was horrid.... and i showered every day, full self care. Cut my own hair... when my ex was at home, she couldnt find time to pee, but she found time to nap 6 hrs, watch 4 hrs of tv, ignore everything until i was home and could do it... and even at its worste, it was still easiest job i ever did. My ex did 1 thing, she folded laundry... not washed or dried, just folded. And it was only frustrating for me when she went out of her way to make things worse and then complain we didnt fold laundry.... like, I did all cleaning, all food, worked, all house maintenance, cut all 3 kids hair, all homework help, all school events, all medical or sick kid care, everything. She folded laundry. And was always too busy to shower except at 2am which she complained about just like this lady...so i have a very valid, but biased reason to doubt why she couldnt already. And this commentators points seem valid, but not based in reality but in false poor me victim world.

title: B0BLYRB87S MEDITHERAPY Wrinkle Fit Mesh Mask: Roller Collagen for Glass Skin
content: Let me tell you a story about wrinkles. Not the charming, character-building kind etched onto the faces of wise old sages, but the sneaky, insidious lines that seemed to appear overnight, mocking my youthful optimism. I‚Äôm in my late thirties, a working mom with two whirlwind kids and a career that demands more hours than there are in a day. Sleep? Luxury. Self-care? A distant, hazy memory. My reflection lately had started to look like a roadmap of sleepless nights and too much stress, and it was honestly starting to get me down. I‚Äôd tried everything. Expensive department store creams that promised miracles (they lied). DIY face masks concocted from questionable ingredients (they stung). Even those gimmicky jade rollers that felt good for about five minutes before I forgot about them again. Nothing seemed to make a dent in the burgeoning landscape of wrinkles around my eyes and forehead. Then, scrolling through Instagram one night (another late night, naturally), a targeted ad caught my eye. The B0BLYRB87S MEDITHERAPY Wrinkle Fit Mesh Mask: Roller Collagen for Glass Skin. It looked‚Ä¶ different. Intriguing. And desperate times call for desperate measures, right? Skeptical, but with nothing to lose, I clicked buy. A few days later, a sleek package arrived, containing this strange, almost futuristic-looking mask. It was a fine mesh material, almost silky to the touch, and came with a small, surprisingly sturdy roller applicator. The instructions were surprisingly simple, but the promise ‚Äì a reduction in wrinkles through collagen application and a cooling, soothing effect ‚Äì was enough to make my eyebrow raise in cautious optimism. The first time I used it, I confess, I felt a little silly. Laying there, this mesh clinging to my face, feeling the cool roller glide across my skin‚Ä¶ it felt oddly luxurious, like a mini-spa day I could afford. And the cooling effect was genuinely soothing. It was a welcome respite from the constant tension I felt in my forehead. The collagen serum, clear and light, absorbed quickly without leaving a sticky residue. I followed the recommended use ‚Äì 15-20 minutes, twice a week ‚Äì diligently, making it part of my (admittedly limited) self-care routine. After a week, I didnt expect miracles, but I noticed something. My skin felt‚Ä¶ firmer. The fine lines around my eyes seemed less pronounced, and my overall complexion looked brighter, more even. After a month, the difference was undeniable. The deep creases around my eyes were visibly reduced. The forehead lines, while not completely gone, were significantly softer. My skin had that coveted glass skin glow the product promised. It wasnt a complete transformation ‚Äì I‚Äôm not suddenly twenty-five again ‚Äì but the improvement was substantial and noticeable. My husband, bless his heart, even commented on it. He‚Äôs not exactly an expert on skincare, but he noticed the change. And that, my friends, is a testament to the effectiveness of the B0BLYRB87S MEDITHERAPY Wrinkle Fit Mesh Mask. This isnt some quick fix, some magic potion that erases years overnight. Its a consistent, effective treatment that, with regular use, yields real, noticeable results. Its become a ritual, a small act of self-care in a hectic life, and the results have been more than worth the investment. So, if youre looking for a way to combat the signs of aging without breaking the bank or spending hours in complicated routines, I highly recommend giving the B0BLYRB87S MEDITHERAPY Wrinkle Fit Mesh Mask a try. It‚Äôs more than just a product; it‚Äôs a small act of self-love that truly makes a difference. You deserve to feel confident in your skin, and this mask helped me get there. Trust me, your future self will thank you. And who knows, maybe youll even get your glass skin glow, too. The results speak for themselves, and I can confidently say that this mask has earned its place in my daily skincare routine. My only regret? Not trying it sooner!

Not in the spa day kind of way but in a way that is loving to yourself on a daily basis. Breathing deeply, saying kind words to yourself and others, spending time in nature, meditating every morning, cultivating self-love and self-acceptance. title: From Bride-to-Be to Besties | Bridesmaid's Tale | Skincare, Laughter & Heartfelt #Ashpveda Surprises
content: The pre-wedding jitters were real. Not just for the bride, but for us bridesmaids too! Amidst the chaos of dress fittings and vendor calls, we found a moment of calm. The bride, bless her heart, surprised us with the most thoughtful gifts ‚Äì beautiful boxes filled with the goodness of #Ashpveda. We laughed, we gossiped, and we applied the face packs, turning our little get-together into a mini spa day. The air was filled with the calming scents of Ayurveda, and the anticipation of the big day began to fade, replaced by a sense of peace and togetherness. As we waited for the masks to dry, we reminisced about countless memories ‚Äì from childhood sleepovers to college escapades, from tearful confessions to wild celebrations. We realized that the bride wasn't just thanking us for being bridesmaids; she was thanking us for being her friends, her family. And then, the bride turned to us and asked, "What's the secret to my smile?" We all knew the answer ‚Äì it was the love and support we shared, the bond that was stronger than any wedding dress. The Ashpveda gifts weren't just about pampering; they were a symbol of gratitude, a reminder that self-care is essential, especially during times of stress. It was a way for the bride to say, "Thank you for being you, for being my rock." And as we gazed at each other, faces glowing with the goodness of Ayurveda and hearts overflowing with love, we knew this was a memory we would cherish forever.

title: Hey there, busy bees! üêù
content: Hey there, busy bees! üêù I know how hectic the week can get, so here's a little guide to help you chill out and recharge over the weekend: 1. **Disconnect**: Turn off those email notifications and give yourself a tech break. Your brain will thank you! What are your favorite ways to unplug from technology? 2. **Move It**: Whether it's yoga, a hike, or just a walk in the park, getting active helps clear your mind. Do you have any favorite spots for outdoor activities? 3. **Eat Well**: Prep some healthy meals in advance. Think simple salads, smoothies, and one-pot wonders that save time but keep you energized. Got any go-to recipes you love? 4. **Pamper Time**: Treat yourself to a spa day at home. A long bath, some candles, and good music can work wonders. What's your ultimate self-care ritual? 5. **Plan Ahead**: Spend a little time planning out your week. It can help reduce stress and keep you focused. How do you stay organized for the week ahead? 6. **Connect**: Catch up with friends or family. Human connection is key to mental wellness. Any fun plans with loved ones this weekend? Ladies, remember to take care of yourselves too! Practice self-care, #love , set boundaries, and don't be afraid to ask for help when you need it. How do you ensure you‚Äôre setting enough boundaries to maintain your mental wellness? Enjoy your weekend and get ready to crush it next week! üí™‚ú® #valuedhr #businessowners #success #virtualassistants #instagood #follow #life

content: üåüSingles Awareness Dayüåü üåüSingles Awareness Day, often abbreviated as SAD, is observed on February 15th, directly following Valentine's Day. It's a more light-hearted or humorous response to the romantic emphasis of Valentine's Day, focusing instead on celebrating singlehood, self-love, and friendship. Here are a few ways people might celebrate or acknowledge Singles Awareness Day: Self-Care: It's a day where singles might treat themselves to something special, like a spa day, a favorite meal, or simply enjoying some alone time doing activities they love. Social Gatherings: Friends might get together for anti-Valentine's parties or other social events that emphasize camaraderie over romantic love. Reflection: Some might use this day to reflect on personal growth, setting goals for self-improvement or considering what they truly want in relationships or life. Humor: There's often a humorous angle, with memes, discounts, or special offers aimed at singles, embracing the day with a bit of irony or jest.

title: Startup Cancer Spa with Saranne
content: In today's episode, we join Saranne, the founder of the Comedy Cures Foundation, as she shares an inspiring story of celebration and pampering amidst the battle against Stage IV cancer. Saranne recounts the heartwarming gesture of her friend Shavit, who surprised their mutual friend Yael with a spa day during her last chemo treatment. The episode explores the incredible impact this unexpected act of kindness had on Yael and the chemo facility and how it inspired a startup company to offer similar services to hospital cancer patients. Join us as we delve into this extraordinary story of resilience, friendship, and the power of self-care in the face of adversity. Ranked the Top 5 Best Cancer Podcasts by CancerCare News in 2024 & 2025, and #1 Rated Cancer Survivor Podcast by FeedSpot in 2024 Beating Cancer Daily is listened to in over 130 countries on 7 continents and has over 365 original daily episodes hosted by Stage IV survivor Saranne Rothberg! title: DIY Facial At Home For Glowing Skin | Coffee Facial At Home | DIY Coffee Facial Hack #ytshorts
content: ‚ú® Transform Your Skin with This DIY Coffee Facial! ‚ú® Say goodbye to dull skin with this 4-step coffee facial that‚Äôs 100% natural and super effective. ‚òïüå∏ Perfect for glowing, soft, and radiant skin at home without spending a fortune at the salon! Full Recipe: 1Ô∏è‚É£ Coffee Cleanser: ‚Ä¢ Mix 2 teaspoons coffee powder with 2 teaspoons raw milk. ‚Ä¢ Gently massage your face for 2-3 minutes to remove dirt, oil, and tan. Wash off with lukewarm water for fresh, clean skin. 2Ô∏è‚É£ Coffee Scrub: ‚Ä¢ Mix 2 teaspoons coffee powder, 1 teaspoon sugar, and 1 teaspoon coconut oil. ‚Ä¢ Apply the scrub in circular motions for 3-5 minutes. This exfoliates dead skin cells, boosts circulation, and makes your skin baby-soft. 3Ô∏è‚É£ Steam: ‚Ä¢ After scrubbing, take steam for 2-3 minutes. Now, let‚Äôs shift gears and talk about skin health. The warm oil used in shirodhara is often infused with herbs that have nourishing properties. This therapy can improve blood circulation to the scalp and face, promoting a healthy glow and potentially reducing signs of aging. Who doesn‚Äôt want that? Another fantastic benefit is its impact on hair health. Regular shirodhara treatments can strengthen hair follicles, reduce hair fall, and even help with dandruff. Your brain will thank you! What are your favorite ways to unplug from technology? 2. **Move It**: Whether it's yoga, a hike, or just a walk in the park, getting active helps clear your mind. Do you have any favorite spots for outdoor activities? 3. **Eat Well**: Prep some healthy meals in advance. Think simple salads, smoothies, and one-pot wonders that save time but keep you energized. Got any go-to recipes you love? 4. **Pamper Time**: Treat yourself to a spa day at home. A long bath, some candles, and good music can work wonders. How do you stay organized for the week ahead? 6. **Connect**: Catch up with friends or family. Human connection is key to mental wellness. Any fun plans with loved ones this weekend? Ladies, remember to take care of yourselves too! Practice self-care, #love , set boundaries, and don't be afraid to ask for help when you need it. title: Hey there, busy bees! üêù
content: Hey there, busy bees! üêù I know how hectic the week can get, so here's a little guide to help you chill out and recharge over the weekend: 1. **Disconnect**: Turn off those email notifications and give yourself a tech break. Your brain will thank you! What are your favorite ways to unplug from technology? 2. **Move It**: Whether it's yoga, a hike, or just a walk in the park, getting active helps clear your mind. Do you have any favorite spots for outdoor activities? 3. **Eat Well**: Prep some healthy meals in advance. Think simple salads, smoothies, and one-pot wonders that save time but keep you energized. Got any go-to recipes you love? 4. **Pamper Time**: Treat yourself to a spa day at home. A long bath, some candles, and good music can work wonders. What's your ultimate self-care ritual? 5. **Plan Ahead**: Spend a little time planning out your week. It can help reduce stress and keep you focused. How do you stay organized for the week ahead? 6. **Connect**: Catch up with friends or family. Human connection is key to mental wellness. Any fun plans with loved ones this weekend? Ladies, remember to take care of yourselves too! Practice self-care, #love , set boundaries, and don't be afraid to ask for help when you need it. How do you ensure you‚Äôre setting enough boundaries to maintain your mental wellness? Enjoy your weekend and get ready to crush it next week! üí™‚ú® #valuedhr #businessowners #success #virtualassistants #instagood #follow #life

title: Self-Care as Healthcare ‚öïÔ∏èand Harnessing the Fresh Start EffectüÜï
content: Self-care has become something of a buzzword, but most of us might only think of a massage or a spa day when we hear it. In fact, self-care is best defined as "ensuring your well-being by tending to emotional or physical needs." It can be as simple as drinking enough water or calling a friend. Self-care is essential. But how do you get it into your life on the daily so that you are able to keep your tank as full as possible? That's what I talk about in this episode. title: Rediscovering self-love, not self-care | Ruby Dhal | TEDxTeessideWomen
content: Ruby Dhal uncovers the relationship between self-love and healing in a culture where chanting 'I love me' to the mirror everyday and drinking your 2 litres after a gym workout are portrayed as enough to practise self-love. Self-love isn‚Äôt just grabbing a caramel latte and having a candlelit bubble bath. Self-love isn‚Äôt just chanting positive affirmations to yourself. Self-love isn‚Äôt just an indoor movie date with your best friend and a tub of Ben and Jerry‚Äôs or a long walk with your dog to the park. Self-love isn‚Äôt just ‚Äòa book and me in a caf√©‚Äô, or a relaxing spa day. It is more than that. But because most of us don‚Äôt search for that ‚Äòmore‚Äô we‚Äôre restricted to this empty practice of self-love that does all the stuff it needs to on the outside ‚Äîwithout fixing anything on the inside. We continue to do all the self-care stuff with the hope that one day it will feel good. That one day we will be truly happy. That one day we will reach a tender place in our healing. We continue to paint our walls without thinking about our collapsing infrastructure. Ruby Dhal is a self-love content creator, poet and bestselling author of 6 books, with a social media following of 1 million. Ruby moved to the UK at the age of three and, within a year, lost her mom. This started Ruby's lifelong healing journey and inspired her to create art to heal hearts all over the world. Ruby currently writes and creates content on mental health, love, heartbreak, grief, loss, moving on, self-love and healing journeys via various social media platforms, with her work garnering millions of impressions each week. In 2017, Ruby was only one of 7 South Asian women in the world to be featured in the Harper‚Äôs Bazaar India Writer Hotlist that year. Ruby's latest book, 'The Path To Self-Love' dives deeper into self-love using a mixture of nurturing prose poetry, personal stories and hard-won insight, exercises and journaling. This talk was given at a TEDx event using the TED conference format but independently organized by a local community. Learn more at https://www.ted.com/tedx

Start here: https://t.co/JQsSpmPGBq üíº Climb the Career Ladder Start preparing for roles like charge nurse or manager. Volunteer for projects, take leadership courses, and polish your CV. Higher roles bring greater impact (and better pay üí∞). üèÉ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Take Your Health Seriously Schedule regular check-ups, eat right, and stay active. title: Unplug, Detox, and Recharge: Renew This Holiday Season
content: #new, #youtubevideos , #youtubeshorts , #motivation , #mindfullness , #unplugged , #detox , #recharge , #renewal , #selfcare , #holidaywellness , #mindfulness , #personalgrowth , #emotionalwellbeing , #socialconnection , #healthylifestyle , #newyeargoals , #positivemindset , #inspirationalstories , #selfimprovement OUTLINE: 00:00:00 Opening 00:00:21 Unplug 00:00:56 Detox 00:01:41 Recharge 00:02:18 Renew 00:02:57 Social and Emotional Well-Being 00:03:24 Closing Shot Unplug, Detox, Recharge, and Renew: Making the Most of Your Holiday Season The holiday season is a perfect time to slow down, reflect, and take care of yourself. Amid the hustle and bustle, it‚Äôs essential to find ways to unplug, detox, recharge, and renew. This guide provides practical steps to help you make the most of this festive period while enhancing your social and emotional well-being and maintaining a positive perspective. Unplug Digital Detox Limit Screen Time: Set specific times during the day to check your devices. Avoid the constant urge to scroll through social media and emails. Social Media Break: Consider taking a break from social media to focus on in-person connections and enjoy the present moment. Digital-Free Zones: Designate certain areas in your home where digital devices are not allowed, such as the dining room or bedroom. This encourages more meaningful interactions with loved ones. Social Connection Quality Time: Spend uninterrupted quality time with family and friends. Engage in activities that foster connection, such as playing board games or cooking together. Community Engagement: Participate in community events or volunteer work. These activities can strengthen your sense of belonging and purpose. Detox Physical Detox Healthy Eating: Incorporate more fruits, vegetables, and whole foods into your diet. Avoid processed foods and excessive sugar. Hydration: Drink plenty of water to help your body flush out toxins. Gentle Exercise: Engage in light exercises such as yoga, walking, or stretching. Physical activity boosts your mood and overall health. Mental Detox Mindfulness Practices: Practice mindfulness techniques such as meditation, deep breathing, or progressive muscle relaxation. Journaling: Write down your thoughts, feelings, and experiences. Journaling can help clear your mind and gain perspective. Nature Time: Spend time outdoors in nature. A walk in the park or a hike can refresh your mind and spirit. Emotional Detox Emotional Awareness: Recognize and understand your emotions. Allow yourself to feel and express them healthily. Positive Self-talk: Replace negative thoughts with positive affirmations. Boost your self-esteem and emotional resilience. Gratitude Practice: Start a gratitude journal and write down things you are thankful for each day. Focusing on gratitude can enhance your emotional well-being. Recharge Rest and Relaxation Quality Sleep: Ensure you get enough quality sleep each night. Create a relaxing bedtime routine and stick to it. Hobbies: Engage in activities you love and enjoy. Whether it‚Äôs reading, painting, or gardening, hobbies can be a great way to relax and recharge. Home Spa Day: Treat yourself to a spa day at home with a warm bath, face masks, and soothing music. Self-care rituals can rejuvenate your body and mind. Social Recharge Reconnect: Reach out to old friends or distant relatives. Reconnecting with loved ones can lift your spirits and strengthen bonds. Social Activities: Plan social activities that bring joy and laughter. Attend festive gatherings or host a holiday party. Renew Personal Growth Set New Goals: Reflect on the past year and set new goals for the upcoming year. Make them specific, achievable, and meaningful. Learn Something New: Take up a new hobby or learn a new skill. This could be anything from cooking a new recipe to learning a language. Self-Reflection: Spend time reflecting on your values, passions, and aspirations. Align your goals with what truly matters to you. Emotional Renewal Embrace Positivity: Surround yourself with positive influences and practice optimism. A positive outlook can enhance your resilience and well-being. Emotional Support: Seek support from loved ones or professionals if needed. Emotional support can provide comfort and guidance during challenging times. Perspective and Mindset Growth Mindset: Embrace challenges and view failures as opportunities to learn and grow. A growth mindset encourages continuous improvement. Perspective Shifts: Regularly reflect on your experiences and adjust your approach as needed. Maintain a flexible and open mindset. @TheRelearningCurve

title: Soak & Relax: From Roman Balneotherapy to Modern Spa
content: Did you know that the origins of spa culture may be traced back to ancient Rome? With their bathhouses, which functioned as social gathering places and wellness centers and provided services like massages, mud baths, and hot spring soaks that were thought to improve health, the Romans were masters of the art of relaxation. These traditional methods have been modified by modern spas, which use hydrotherapy, aromatherapy, and mineral baths to help patrons unwind and revitalize. You're taking part in an ancient self-care practice that dates back to the Roman Empire by treating yourself to a spa day. title: Hey there, busy bees! üêù
content: Hey there, busy bees! üêù I know how hectic the week can get, so here's a little guide to help you chill out and recharge over the weekend: 1. **Disconnect**: Turn off those email notifications and give yourself a tech break. Your brain will thank you! What are your favorite ways to unplug from technology? 2. **Move It**: Whether it's yoga, a hike, or just a walk in the park, getting active helps clear your mind. Do you have any favorite spots for outdoor activities? 3. **Eat Well**: Prep some healthy meals in advance. Think simple salads, smoothies, and one-pot wonders that save time but keep you energized. Got any go-to recipes you love? 4. **Pamper Time**: Treat yourself to a spa day at home. A long bath, some candles, and good music can work wonders. What's your ultimate self-care ritual? 5. **Plan Ahead**: Spend a little time planning out your week. It can help reduce stress and keep you focused. How do you stay organized for the week ahead? 6. **Connect**: Catch up with friends or family. Human connection is key to mental wellness. Any fun plans with loved ones this weekend? Ladies, remember to take care of yourselves too! Practice self-care, #love , set boundaries, and don't be afraid to ask for help when you need it. How do you ensure you‚Äôre setting enough boundaries to maintain your mental wellness? Enjoy your weekend and get ready to crush it next week! üí™‚ú® #valuedhr #businessowners #success #virtualassistants #instagood #follow #life

title: Beyond the Spa Day: Redefining Self-Care for Resilient Women
content: Podcast Show Notes: Title: Beyond the Spa Day: Redefining Self-Care for Resilient Women Host: Kathryn Regganie Guest: Kimberly Lechnick Episode Summary: In this episode of Resilient Woman Leadership, Kathryn Regganie and guest Kimberly Lechnick dive deep into the often-misunderstood world of self-care, emotional intelligence, and somatic healing. Together, they explore how foundational practices like honoring your core values, prioritizing self-partnership, and making space for curiosity in conflict can become game-changers in both personal and professional leadership. This conversation challenges the surface-level view of self-care and invites you into a much more holistic perspective‚Äîone where leadership begins within the body, and emotional awareness is a strength, not a liability. Key Topics Discussed: How emotional intelligence helps navigate misunderstandings with grace The power of getting curious rather than defensive in conflict Why partnering with yourself is essential for empowered decision-making A deeper take on self-care: beyond massages and manicures How somatic bodywork helps process stored trauma The role of core values in aligned leadership and life choices Speaker Bio: Kimberly Lechnick is a relationship coach known for her expertise in guiding individuals and couples toward fulfilling and harmonious relationships. With a passion for helping people navigate the complexities of life and business, Kimberly brings a unique blend of compassion, wisdom, and practical tools to her coaching practice. Drawing from her extensive background in psychology and human behavior, Kimberly empowers her clients to understand their own needs and desires while fostering open and effective communication with key people in their business and personal life. Her approach is deeply rooted in empathy, ensuring a safe space for individuals to explore their emotions, fears, and aspirations. title: I went to my local spa and fell in love with their gorgeous plant paradise! #shorts
content: Going to a spa for self-care offers numerous benefits, both physically and mentally. Here are the main advantages: Physical Benefits Muscle Relaxation ‚Äì Massages help relieve tension, reduce soreness, and improve flexibility. Improved Circulation ‚Äì Treatments like hydrotherapy and hot stone massages enhance blood flow, promoting better oxygenation of cells. Detoxification ‚Äì Saunas, steam rooms, and body wraps help flush out toxins and cleanse the skin. Pain Relief ‚Äì Spa treatments can alleviate chronic pain, headaches, and joint stiffness. Better Sleep ‚Äì Relaxation therapies help reduce stress, leading to improved sleep quality. Glowing Skin ‚Äì Facials and exfoliation treatments rejuvenate the skin, reducing signs of aging and promoting hydration. Mental & Emotional Benefits Stress Reduction ‚Äì The calming environment and treatments help lower cortisol levels, reducing anxiety and stress. Boosted Mood ‚Äì Massages and aromatherapy stimulate serotonin and dopamine production, enhancing overall well-being. Increased Mindfulness ‚Äì Spa visits encourage slowing down and being present, fostering mindfulness. Emotional Release ‚Äì Some treatments, like deep-tissue massages or aromatherapy, can help release stored emotions and tension. Holistic & Long-Term Benefits Improved Immune System ‚Äì Regular spa visits help regulate stress hormones and support the body's natural defenses. Enhanced Productivity ‚Äì Taking time for self-care boosts mental clarity, focus, and overall efficiency in daily life. Self-Confidence Boost ‚Äì Feeling refreshed and pampered enhances self-esteem and promotes a positive self-image. Preventive Health Care ‚Äì Regular treatments can help prevent physical ailments by maintaining balance in the body. A spa day is more than just a luxury‚Äîit's a valuable investment in overall well-being. Treat yourself today!

title: Essential Spa Tips
content: Maximize your spa day at Riviera Health Spa with these expert tips! Self-care made easy. 1Ô∏è‚É£ Hydrate: Drink plenty of water before, during, and after your visit to stay hydrated and enhance the detoxification benefits of the sauna. 2Ô∏è‚É£ Arrive early: Give yourself time to check in, change, and explore the facilities before your treatments. 3Ô∏è‚É£ Try the different saunas: Each sauna offers unique benefits, from detoxification to muscle relaxation. title: Hey there, busy bees! üêù
content: Hey there, busy bees! üêù I know how hectic the week can get, so here's a little guide to help you chill out and recharge over the weekend: 1. **Disconnect**: Turn off those email notifications and give yourself a tech break. Your brain will thank you! What are your favorite ways to unplug from technology? 2. **Move It**: Whether it's yoga, a hike, or just a walk in the park, getting active helps clear your mind. Do you have any favorite spots for outdoor activities? 3. **Eat Well**: Prep some healthy meals in advance. Think simple salads, smoothies, and one-pot wonders that save time but keep you energized. Got any go-to recipes you love? 4. **Pamper Time**: Treat yourself to a spa day at home. A long bath, some candles, and good music can work wonders. What's your ultimate self-care ritual? 5. **Plan Ahead**: Spend a little time planning out your week. It can help reduce stress and keep you focused. How do you stay organized for the week ahead? 6. **Connect**: Catch up with friends or family. Human connection is key to mental wellness. Any fun plans with loved ones this weekend? Ladies, remember to take care of yourselves too! Practice self-care, #love , set boundaries, and don't be afraid to ask for help when you need it. How do you ensure you‚Äôre setting enough boundaries to maintain your mental wellness? Enjoy your weekend and get ready to crush it next week! üí™‚ú® #valuedhr #businessowners #success #virtualassistants #instagood #follow #life

title: 5 Tips to Keep Your Holidays Joyful and Juicy (Even If You're Busy AF)
content: Feeling overwhelmed by the endless holiday to-do lists? Craving more connection and joy, but barely have time to breathe? Here's the truth: The magic of the season isn't in perfect decorations or Pinterest-worthy gatherings. It's in those small, delicious moments that are already woven into your days ‚Äì if you know how to access them. content: üåû Good Morning my Friends! üåü It's Saturday, the glorious middle of the weekend, and the perfect time to do something purely for our own fun. Today, let's embrace the joy of living and make the most out of every moment. Here are some exciting ideas to make your Saturday extra special: 1. Outdoor Adventure: Step outside and soak up the fresh air! Whether it‚Äôs hiking, biking, or just a leisurely walk in the park, nature has a way of refreshing our spirits and energizing our minds. 2. Creative Pursuits: Unleash your inner artist! Paint, draw, write, or craft something unique. Creativity is a fantastic way to express yourself and relax. Who knows, you might discover a hidden talent! 3. Indulge in a Hobby: Dive into your favorite hobby, whether it‚Äôs gardening, cooking, reading, or playing an instrument. Doing what you love is the best way to recharge and find joy. 4. Movie Marathon: Gather some snacks, cozy up with a blanket, and binge-watch your favorite movies or series. It's the perfect excuse to relax and enjoy some screen time guilt-free. 5. Pamper Yourself: Treat yourself to a spa day at home. Run a bubble bath, light some candles, and play soothing music. Self-care is essential, and you deserve to feel pampered and relaxed. 6. Connect with Loved Ones: Spend quality time with family or friends. Have a picnic, play games, or simply chat over a cup of coffee. Human connection is vital for happiness and well-being. 7. Try Something New: Step out of your comfort zone and try something you‚Äôve never done before. It could be a new recipe, a new workout routine, or learning a new skill. The thrill of new experiences can be incredibly invigorating. 8. Laugh Out Loud: Watch a comedy show, read funny jokes, or play a fun game. Laughter is the best medicine, and it‚Äôs a fantastic way to lift your spirits and enjoy the day. 9. Enjoy the Simple Pleasures: Sometimes, the simplest things bring the most joy. Enjoy a leisurely breakfast, take a nap, or sit in the garden with a good book. Savor the moment and appreciate the beauty of a relaxed day. 10. Plan Your Next Adventure: If you‚Äôre feeling inspired, start planning your next trip or adventure. Dreaming about future fun can be just as exciting as the real thing. title: Hey there, busy bees! üêù
content: Hey there, busy bees! üêù I know how hectic the week can get, so here's a little guide to help you chill out and recharge over the weekend: 1. **Disconnect**: Turn off those email notifications and give yourself a tech break. Your brain will thank you! What are your favorite ways to unplug from technology? 2. **Move It**: Whether it's yoga, a hike, or just a walk in the park, getting active helps clear your mind. Do you have any favorite spots for outdoor activities? 3. **Eat Well**: Prep some healthy meals in advance. Think simple salads, smoothies, and one-pot wonders that save time but keep you energized. Got any go-to recipes you love? 4. **Pamper Time**: Treat yourself to a spa day at home. A long bath, some candles, and good music can work wonders. What's your ultimate self-care ritual? 5. **Plan Ahead**: Spend a little time planning out your week. It can help reduce stress and keep you focused. How do you stay organized for the week ahead? 6. **Connect**: Catch up with friends or family. Human connection is key to mental wellness. Any fun plans with loved ones this weekend? Ladies, remember to take care of yourselves too! Practice self-care, #love , set boundaries, and don't be afraid to ask for help when you need it. How do you ensure you‚Äôre setting enough boundaries to maintain your mental wellness? Enjoy your weekend and get ready to crush it next week! üí™‚ú® #valuedhr #businessowners #success #virtualassistants #instagood #follow #life

title: Are you mothering yourself enough?
content: Ever paused to think about who is taking care of you? In our latest episode of 'Renew Motherhood', we dive into a radical idea with Nina Robert: the importance of mothering yourself. Nina's insights are a wake-up call. Most of us operate on autopilot, driven by subconscious beliefs and attitudes we aren't even aware of. It's not just about taking that spa day or treating yourself to a fancy dinner. It's about digging deep, getting curious, and bravely questioning the narratives that guide us. Our conversation challenges the traditional view of motherhood. It's not just about nurturing others, but also about turning that nurturing inward. It's about asking the tough questions and being honest with yourself. This isn't the usual self-care advice. It's a shift in mindset ‚Äì a call to mother yourself with the same love and attention you give to others. Because let's face it, how can you pour from an empty cup?

title: Hey there, busy bees! üêù
content: Hey there, busy bees! üêù I know how hectic the week can get, so here's a little guide to help you chill out and recharge over the weekend: 1. **Disconnect**: Turn off those email notifications and give yourself a tech break. Your brain will thank you! What are your favorite ways to unplug from technology? 2. **Move It**: Whether it's yoga, a hike, or just a walk in the park, getting active helps clear your mind. Do you have any favorite spots for outdoor activities? 3. **Eat Well**: Prep some healthy meals in advance. Think simple salads, smoothies, and one-pot wonders that save time but keep you energized. Got any go-to recipes you love? 4. **Pamper Time**: Treat yourself to a spa day at home. A long bath, some candles, and good music can work wonders. What's your ultimate self-care ritual? 5. **Plan Ahead**: Spend a little time planning out your week. It can help reduce stress and keep you focused. How do you stay organized for the week ahead? 6. **Connect**: Catch up with friends or family. Human connection is key to mental wellness. Any fun plans with loved ones this weekend? Ladies, remember to take care of yourselves too! Practice self-care, #love , set boundaries, and don't be afraid to ask for help when you need it. How do you ensure you‚Äôre setting enough boundaries to maintain your mental wellness? Enjoy your weekend and get ready to crush it next week! üí™‚ú® #valuedhr #businessowners #success #virtualassistants #instagood #follow #life

Your brain will thank you! What are your favorite ways to unplug from technology? 2. **Move It**: Whether it's yoga, a hike, or just a walk in the park, getting active helps clear your mind. title: Unwind in Baku: The 5 Best Spa Retreats!
content: Indulge in ultimate relaxation at Baku's top 5 spa destinations, where wellness and tranquillity meet modern luxury. Whether you're a local seeking a quick escape or a traveller looking to unwind after exploring the vibrant city, these exquisite spas offer the perfect sanctuary. Gazelli House: A haven of indulgence, Gazelli House is known for its luxurious treatments that combine tradition with modern expertise. From rejuvenating facials to therapeutic massages, this spa is where relaxation meets elegance. Gazelli's signature treatments use the finest organic ingredients, leaving you feeling refreshed, pampered, and revitalized. Whether you're looking to unwind or indulge in advanced skincare treatments, Gazelli House promises a memorable experience. It's not just a spa; it's an escape into serenity. Hamambath: Immerse yourself in the ancient traditions of a Turkish bath at Baku's renowned Hamambath. This experience takes you back in time, offering a holistic detox with steam, scrubs, and massages that cleanse both body and soul. The Hamam ritual has been practiced for centuries, and it's a must-try for anyone looking to purify and relax deeply. The heat and steam open up your pores, while the invigorating scrub rejuvenates your skin, leaving you feeling light, refreshed, and completely relaxed. It‚Äôs the ultimate traditional wellness experience. Art Lab: For those seeking a more holistic approach to wellness, Art Lab is the place to be. This cutting-edge spa focuses on personalised wellness journeys, integrating beauty, health, and fitness into their treatments. From deep-tissue massages to aromatherapy, each treatment is designed to balance both body and mind. Art Lab's focus on innovative techniques and natural products makes it a favourite for those who appreciate a well-rounded approach to self-care. Whether you're detoxing, energising, or simply relaxing, Art Lab has something for everyone. Kepro Spa: Renowned for its skincare expertise, Kepro Spa offers a wide array of treatments designed to rejuvenate your skin. Specialising in anti-ageing therapies, facials, and body treatments, Kepro uses top-tier products to give your skin the attention it deserves. Their skincare rituals, combined with the calming atmosphere, make it an ideal destination for those who want to focus on skin health while enjoying the benefits of a spa retreat. At Kepro, it's not just about relaxation‚Äîit's about restoring your skin's natural glow. Seven Beauties Spa: Escape into a serene retreat at Seven Beauties, where the calming atmosphere instantly transports you into a world of peace and tranquillity. This spa offers a wide range of treatments designed to relax, rejuvenate, and refresh your entire being. With a focus on traditional techniques and a peaceful environment, Seven Beauties is the ideal place to unwind and reconnect with yourself. title: Hey there, busy bees! üêù
content: Hey there, busy bees! üêù I know how hectic the week can get, so here's a little guide to help you chill out and recharge over the weekend: 1. **Disconnect**: Turn off those email notifications and give yourself a tech break. Your brain will thank you! What are your favorite ways to unplug from technology? 2. **Move It**: Whether it's yoga, a hike, or just a walk in the park, getting active helps clear your mind. Do you have any favorite spots for outdoor activities? 3. **Eat Well**: Prep some healthy meals in advance. Think simple salads, smoothies, and one-pot wonders that save time but keep you energized. Got any go-to recipes you love? 4. **Pamper Time**: Treat yourself to a spa day at home. A long bath, some candles, and good music can work wonders. What's your ultimate self-care ritual? 5. **Plan Ahead**: Spend a little time planning out your week. It can help reduce stress and keep you focused. How do you stay organized for the week ahead? 6. **Connect**: Catch up with friends or family. Human connection is key to mental wellness. Any fun plans with loved ones this weekend? Ladies, remember to take care of yourselves too! Practice self-care, #love , set boundaries, and don't be afraid to ask for help when you need it. How do you ensure you‚Äôre setting enough boundaries to maintain your mental wellness? Enjoy your weekend and get ready to crush it next week! üí™‚ú® #valuedhr #businessowners #success #virtualassistants #instagood #follow #life

title: Hey there, busy bees! üêù
content: Hey there, busy bees! üêù I know how hectic the week can get, so here's a little guide to help you chill out and recharge over the weekend: 1. **Disconnect**: Turn off those email notifications and give yourself a tech break. Your brain will thank you! What are your favorite ways to unplug from technology? 2. **Move It**: Whether it's yoga, a hike, or just a walk in the park, getting active helps clear your mind. Do you have any favorite spots for outdoor activities? 3. **Eat Well**: Prep some healthy meals in advance. Think simple salads, smoothies, and one-pot wonders that save time but keep you energized. Got any go-to recipes you love? 4. **Pamper Time**: Treat yourself to a spa day at home. A long bath, some candles, and good music can work wonders. What's your ultimate self-care ritual? 5. **Plan Ahead**: Spend a little time planning out your week. It can help reduce stress and keep you focused. How do you stay organized for the week ahead? 6. **Connect**: Catch up with friends or family. Human connection is key to mental wellness. Any fun plans with loved ones this weekend? Ladies, remember to take care of yourselves too! Practice self-care, #love , set boundaries, and don't be afraid to ask for help when you need it. How do you ensure you‚Äôre setting enough boundaries to maintain your mental wellness? Enjoy your weekend and get ready to crush it next week! üí™‚ú® #valuedhr #businessowners #success #virtualassistants #instagood #follow #life

content: Hey there, busy bees! üêù I know how hectic the week can get, so here's a little guide to help you chill out and recharge over the weekend: 1. **Disconnect**: Turn off those email notifications and give yourself a tech break. Do you have any favorite spots for outdoor activities? 3. **Eat Well**: Prep some healthy meals in advance. Think simple salads, smoothies, and one-pot wonders that save time but keep you energized. Got any go-to recipes you love? 4. **Pamper Time**: Treat yourself to a spa day at home. A long bath, some candles, and good music can work wonders. What's your ultimate self-care ritual? 5. **Plan Ahead**: Spend a little time planning out your week. It can help reduce stress and keep you focused. How do you stay organized for the week ahead? 6. **Connect**: Catch up with friends or family. Human connection is key to mental wellness. Any fun plans with loved ones this weekend? Ladies, remember to take care of yourselves too! Practice self-care, #love , set boundaries, and don't be afraid to ask for help when you need it. How do you ensure you‚Äôre setting enough boundaries to maintain your mental wellness? content: It's sucks, but it's true. I've been playing since the beginning... so I accumulated most of the packs over time. I can't imagine being greeted with all this dlc if I started playing today. Ea basically gave us a boring game and has been slowly drip feeding us content to fulfill the void of how empty the base game felt. There are still things even 10 years that we're missing that would be nice to have. Like Drums, other instruments, create a band, touring, gigs, (the entertainment rabbit hole career is awful)  Expansions packs usually only add rabbit hole careers, some gameplay, & a wide variety of themes for build / cas Gamepacks - in my opinion adds the most value to the game itself for the price Stuff packs- Nice to haves, but generally not needed Kits - niche vibes & aesthethics, depends on your style and type of simmer you're  Paranormal / Goth essentials Vampires, werewolves, magic, life & death, paranormal pack, crystal creations, spooky, goth galore, grunge revival, castle, story book  The eco / off the grid / country rancher / minimalist roleplay  Industrial kit / eco lifestyle / green house kit / tiny living / country / cottage living / blooming room / nifty knitting / laundry day / outdoor retreat / island / seasons /snowy escape / bust the dust / horse ranch  Relaxation / healthy living / self care desert luxe / spa day / fitness pack (has great build items i love it)  "fun packs, excitement, luxory) movie pack / bowling night / city living / get to work, get famous / luxory packs / moschino stuff / get famous / for rent / vintage glamour  Take a vacation (great for families outdoor reteat / little campers / snow escape /  Family simmers high school / uni / parenthood / growing together / kid packs / toddler packs / life & death (everything else is just icing on the cake)  Gold digger simmers collection lovestruck / wedding stories / romantic gardens / simtimate collections / + clothing ktis or any pack that has a certain vibe for your sims  Home decorator - basically any pack with build mode items you'll probably want it all if you enjoy building things I guess  Get rich not so quick schemes packs dine out / for rent / cats and dogs / retail< get to work  Traveler / adventure / story packs Jungle adventure, strangerville, star wars

title: How Beauty Salons Boost the Economy: The Power of Hair & Beauty Industry! üíá‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èüíÖ
content: Did you know that your trip to the hair salon is more than just a chance to refresh your look? The beauty and hair salon industry is one of the most significant contributors to the economy, and every visit you make plays a role in this multi-billion-dollar industry. Whether you're getting a simple haircut, a luxurious facial, or a full makeover, you're helping to drive growth, create jobs, and support local businesses. In the United States, the beauty and personal care industry generates over $60 billion in annual revenue. This includes everything from haircuts and skincare treatments to makeup, nails, and spa services. Beauty salons, spas, and wellness centers aren't just places for personal transformation‚Äîthey‚Äôre economic powerhouses that impact everything from small, family-owned shops to larger, global beauty brands. When you step into a salon, you're not just investing in your appearance‚Äîyou're supporting an entire network of professionals. The beauty industry employs millions of people across the country, from hairstylists and makeup artists to estheticians, nail technicians, and salon managers. These businesses provide stable income for workers, many of whom rely on tips and commissions, and create opportunities for entrepreneurship. Salon owners and beauty entrepreneurs also contribute to their local economies by paying taxes, buying products, and hiring staff. But it doesn‚Äôt stop there‚Äîbeauty salons and wellness centers also stimulate other industries. For example, beauty supply companies, product manufacturers, beauty schools, and even tech companies that create salon management software all benefit from the thriving beauty sector. From shampoo to high-end skincare lines, the beauty industry fuels demand for thousands of products, making it a critical part of the global supply chain. As more people prioritize self-care and personal wellness, the demand for beauty services continues to rise. In fact, many women and men now see their visits to beauty centers as essential not just for their appearance but for their mental and emotional well-being. The "self-care" movement has led to more people investing in themselves, creating a growing demand for everything from hair color and cuts to skin rejuvenation and wellness treatments. Moreover, beauty businesses contribute to the local economy by attracting customers who spend money on products, services, and experiences. Salons often create a sense of community, bringing people together in a way that benefits the local area. Whether it‚Äôs a new salon opening in your neighborhood or an established spa that brings in clients from out of town, these businesses boost foot traffic, create jobs, and help support other local shops and restaurants. As you get pampered in a salon chair or enjoy a relaxing facial, remember that you're playing a part in a much larger economic ecosystem. Each service you purchase helps sustain an industry that not only makes you feel better on the outside but also keeps the economy thriving on the inside. So, the next time you treat yourself to a hair makeover or spa day, you're not just making yourself feel good‚Äîyou‚Äôre helping drive an entire economy forward. Beauty isn‚Äôt just about looks‚Äîit‚Äôs about the power of an industry that touches millions of lives and contributes to economic growth every single day. Support local salons, enjoy your beauty routine, and remember: you‚Äôre making a real impact! üíá‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èüíÖüí∞

title: Hey there, busy bees! üêù
content: Hey there, busy bees! üêù I know how hectic the week can get, so here's a little guide to help you chill out and recharge over the weekend: 1. **Disconnect**: Turn off those email notifications and give yourself a tech break. Your brain will thank you! What are your favorite ways to unplug from technology? 2. **Move It**: Whether it's yoga, a hike, or just a walk in the park, getting active helps clear your mind. Do you have any favorite spots for outdoor activities? 3. **Eat Well**: Prep some healthy meals in advance. Think simple salads, smoothies, and one-pot wonders that save time but keep you energized. Got any go-to recipes you love? 4. **Pamper Time**: Treat yourself to a spa day at home. A long bath, some candles, and good music can work wonders. What's your ultimate self-care ritual? 5. **Plan Ahead**: Spend a little time planning out your week. It can help reduce stress and keep you focused. How do you stay organized for the week ahead? 6. **Connect**: Catch up with friends or family. Human connection is key to mental wellness. Any fun plans with loved ones this weekend? Ladies, remember to take care of yourselves too! Practice self-care, #love , set boundaries, and don't be afraid to ask for help when you need it. How do you ensure you‚Äôre setting enough boundaries to maintain your mental wellness? title: S2, E3: Goddess Series - Sulis
content: Sulis is a deity worshiped at the thermal spring of Bath. She was worshiped by the Romano-British as Sulis Minerva, whose votive objects and inscribed lead tablets. Her symbols are water, wheat cakes and fire. The Celtic Goddess Sulis oversees all sacred wells and springs, which give healing and other blessings to those who pray at them. She also has associations with the sun, which explains the ever-burning fires in Her temples. Her symbols are water, wheat cakes and fire. The Celtic Goddess Sulis oversees all sacred wells and springs, which give healing and other blessings to those who pray at them. She also has associations with the sun, which explains the ever-burning fires in Her temples. Sulis is not the same as the Roman goddess Minerva, even though the two figures were combined and worshiped as Sulis Minerva following the Roman conquest of Britain. ‚Å†https://journeyingtothegoddess.wordpress.com/2012/05/27/goddess-sulis/‚Å† If a spa isn‚Äôt possible, let your bathroom get really steamy from a hot-water shower, then sit inside for awhile absorbing Sulis‚Äôs cleansing power into your pores. Release you tensions and dis-ease to Her. Maybe light a candle to represent Sulis‚Äôs presence with you, and meditate as you relax. Remember, the bathroom is one of the few places you can be assured of a private moment with the Goddess, so take advantage of it!‚Äù ‚Å†https://orderwhitemoon.org/goddess/Sulis/Sulis.htm‚Å† Symbols: Water, wheat cakes, fire, sacred wells, springs, and self-care. Provider of healing waters. Cauldron Festival Day: May 1st Beltane Shrine or Holy Place: Bath England, Aquae Sulis. Element: Water and Fire Colors: Gold, Yellow, Blue, and Green Incense: Cinnamon, cloves, frankincense, and laurel Plants: Acacia, Bay laurel, chamomile, citrus fruits, marigold, and sunflower. Trees: Acacia, ash, bay laurel, birch Animals: Eagle, lion, owl, bear, and phoenix DAILY PRACTICE SUGGESTIONS Bless a yellow hair tie, ribbon, or scarf to wear in your hair.Use "sun water" (sterile water that's been sitting in the sun) to rinse your face in your daily face cleansing ritual.Incorporate bay leaves into a recipe OR make a recipe that calls for bay leaves.Volunteer or get involved with your local Audubon society or wildlife/Owl/Eagle rescue.Plant sunflowers or buy a bouquet for your home. (You could also plant any of the plants listed as sacred to Sulis in honor of her.)Drink a cup of chamomile tea during/before/or after the meditation below.Have a spa day! Visit a local spa or indulge in a day of self-care at home. You‚Äôre a time filler, something she squeezes in between Zoom meetings, spin class, and wine nights with her equally ‚Äúbooked and busy‚Äù friends. Your relationship becomes a negotiation. You fight for slivers of her time, attention, and affection. But her energy? That‚Äôs spent. Given to her boss, her clients, her feed. title: Allure Nails and Spa Midland, TX
content: Allure Nails and Spa Midland, TX What services does Allure Nails & Spa provide? Allure Nails and Spa in Midland, TX offers a variety of cosmetic and nail services to make you feel polished and pampered. We specialize in manicures, pedicures, acrylic and gel nails, dip powder, unique nail art, and nail repairs. Our professionals also provide skilled waxing procedures for the face and body, resulting in smooth, glowing skin. For those seeking deeper relaxation, we offer spa services such as paraffin wax therapy and deluxe spa pedicures. We only use high-quality ingredients and cutting-edge processes to assure long-lasting, stunning results. Whether you're getting ready for a special occasion or simply treating yourself to some self-care, our team will develop a unique experience based on your style, tastes, and beauty objectives. What spa treatments do you provide? Allure Nails and Spa provides a variety of spa treatments aimed at rejuvenating and refreshing. Our luxury pedicures include soothing foot soaks, exfoliating washes, callus treatment, moisturizing masks, and relaxing foot and calves massage therapy. We also offer paraffin wax treatments for the hands and feet to deeply hydrate and soothe dry, fatigued skin. Clients who want a little additional pampering can get hot stone massages throughout their pedicure appointment for added relaxation. Our waxing services include facial areas such as brows, lips, and chin, as well as broader areas such as the arms, legs, and bikini. Each spa treatment is carried out with the utmost care, using high-quality, skin-friendly materials in a calm and sanitary setting, resulting in a really delightful experience. What are Allure Nails and Spa's operating hours? Allure Nails and Spa is committed to providing convenient service hours to accommodate your busy schedule. We are open Monday through Saturday from 9:30 a.m. to 7:00 p.m., giving ample possibilities for both weekday and weekend visits. On Sundays, we are open from 12:00 PM to 5:00 PM, ideal for a leisurely afternoon of self-care. Whether you're looking for a fast nail appointment during your lunch break or a longer, decadent spa session on your day off, our flexible hours are tailored to meet your needs. We encourage scheduling appointments in advance, especially on weekends, as those periods tend to fill up quickly. Walk-ins are accepted whenever possible, and we endeavor to give timely, attentive treatment to all clients. Do I need to schedule an appointment? While walk-ins are always welcome at Allure Nails and Spa when space allows, we strongly advise scheduling an appointment to guarantee you get the service and time slot you choose. Appointments help to reduce wait time and allow us to better prepare for your tailored experience, particularly for more elaborate services such as custom nail art, group bookings, and spa packages. Weekends, holidays, and late afternoons are our busiest times, so scheduling in advance is extremely crucial. We value flexibility and try our best to accommodate last-minute appointments wherever possible. Whether you're planning a simple polish change or a full spa day, scheduling your place ensures a seamless and comfortable experience. How can I schedule an appointment at Allure Nails and Spa?. Scheduling an appointment at Allure Nails and Spa is simple and convenient. You can phone us directly during business hours to talk with a pleasant staff member who will assist you in scheduling your service. For added convenience, we provide online booking through our website or social media links, allowing you to select your desired time and technician. Walk-in appointments are allowed if there is availability, but for guaranteed service, particularly for larger groups or specialty treatments, we recommend booking ahead of time. If you need to cancel or reschedule, please tell us at least 24 hours in advance. Our objective is to make the booking procedure as easy and convenient as your time with us. Visit us online: https://www.ellevatemawc.com/west-chester/ https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=voNwZr3jmQM Our Address: Allure Nails and Spa 3303 N Midkiff Rd Ste #191 Midland, TX 79705 (432) 699-1617 https://www.google.com/maps/place/?cid=15642403200695223142 https://sites.google.com/view/allurenailsandspa-midland-tx/ Find us around the web: Like us on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/AllureNailsAndSpaMidlandTX/ Follow us on Twitter: https://x.com/AllureMidlandTX Tiktok URL: https://www.tiktok.com/@allurenailsandspamidland Subscribe to our YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLnSIDqKclbaGsqoPDruibWvmMDBkg0NjL Find us on SoundCloud: https://soundcloud.com/allure-nails-and-spa-midland-tx/allure-nails-and-spa-midland Listen to our BuzzSprout Podcasts: https://www.buzzsprout.com/2497640/episodes/17061555

Between the long shifts, emotional demands, and ever-changing healthcare landscape, it can feel overwhelming. That‚Äôs why 2025 should be the year we focus on thriving, not just surviving. Here‚Äôs how: ü©∫ Self-Care You can‚Äôt pour from an empty cup. Whether it‚Äôs a spa day or Netflix binge, recharging is non-negotiable. Burnout is real, and happy nurses mean healthier patients‚Äîso pamper yourself guilt-free! üìö Invest in Education & Trainings Ready to level up? Take leadership or specialist courses. Get that degree or master‚Äôs this year. Scholarships like UNICAF make it affordable. Start here: https://t.co/JQsSpmPGBq üíº Climb the Career Ladder Start preparing for roles like charge nurse or manager. Volunteer for projects, take leadership courses, and polish your CV. Higher roles bring greater impact (and better pay üí∞). üèÉ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Take Your Health Seriously Schedule regular check-ups, eat right, and stay active. Walking the talk makes you a better nurse and keeps you at your best. üì± Leverage Social Media Social media isn‚Äôt just for memes (though we love themü§£). Use LinkedIn to network, share insights, and maybe build your brand. I have Leveraged social media for a few years now and I can attest that it helps in professional and personal growth. ü§ù Network Like a Pro Conferences aren‚Äôt just for free pens (though they‚Äôre great!). Meet industry leaders, learn new skills, and open unexpected doors. Join your unions conference, Congress etc. üè† Prioritize Loved Ones Make time for family and friends‚Äîthey‚Äôre your biggest cheerleaders. Work-life balance makes you happier and more grounded. if your spouse isn't supporting you, you won't be able to pick that extra shift or take on that course. üè¢ Master Workplace Dynamics Learn the rules of the game at work. title: You don‚Äôt need another spa day ü´£ Because here‚Äôs the truth‚Ä¶ You can get your nails done, soak in a
content: You don‚Äôt need another spa day ü´£ Because here‚Äôs the truth‚Ä¶ You can get your nails done, soak in a tub, and watch an entire season of Love Is Blind (guilty as charged ü§≠) and still wake up the next day wired, tired, anxious, and snapping at your kids before breakfast. Self-care isn‚Äôt working because you‚Äôre not actually supporting your nervous system. You‚Äôre just numbing it. Real talk? If your body‚Äôs stuck in fight-or-flight, no amount of Netflix or pedicures will touch that level of stress. The kind of stress that leaves you: ‚ùå Snapping at your kids before 9am ‚ùå Forgetting what you walked into a room for ‚ùå Feeling exhausted even after a full night‚Äôs sleep ‚ùå Pushing through another day with tight shoulders, clenched jaw, and a to-do list that never ends That kind of stress doesn‚Äôt respond to a bubble bath. It responds to regulation. What regulation actually looks like: ‚úÖ Putting your red light therapy patches on and saying affirmations before the chaos begins ‚úÖ Sipping your greens drink and protein before before your first cup of coffee ‚úÖ Breathing from your belly, not your chest - like taking a break while folding your laundry and putting your hand on your belly to feel it rise and fall kind of belly breathing ‚úÖ Taking micro-movement breaks while doing the dishes for the 7th time today ‚úÖ Actually pausing to notice how your feet feel on the floor beneath instead of powering through when you feel yourself getting escalated as your child bounces around the room screaming instead of sitting down for dinner. This is the kind of self-care that actually works. Because it supports your nervous system, not just your calendar. So if you‚Äôre constantly burned out but still doing all the ‚Äúright‚Äù things‚Ä¶ This is your permission slip to stop chasing aesthetics‚Äîand start healing from the inside out. Save this post if your body has been begging for a new kind of self-care. Tag your over-functioning bestie who really needs to hear this. And if you want support building a nervous-system-first routine that works in real life (yes, even with kids and chaos) ‚Ä¶ DM me ‚ÄúREGULATE‚Äù and I‚Äôll send you a few tools you can start today.

title: Girls Trip Spa Day Vlog | Luxurious Miami Beach Carillon Spa & Resort
content: Spending the day at the Carillon Miami Beach Resort & Spa with the Girls. Finally taking a self-care day and enjoying some luxurious quality time with friends. A luxury spa day is just what we needed and came right on time. Thanks, M for pushing us to do something nice for ourselves FINALLY lol. The Carillon Spa was so aesthetically beautiful and relaxing. Their staff was exceptional and we all left feeling so good. We did all of the spa amenities inside due to the weather... but the amazing hot tub was surrounded by heated lounge chairs underneath a starry-lit domed ceiling with a circular skylight portal that gave the Luxury Spa an ethereal feeling. Although I didn't get any footage of the Wet and Dry Heat Steam Rooms (for the privacy of fellow patrons) they were absolutely AHHMAZING! We also braved the Cold room which was surprisingly not bad, I followed it up with checking out the scented rainforest experience showers with ambient nature sounds and light shows. we arrived a few minutes late but my Massage was incredible, and I didn't feel rushed at all. My Therapist gave me a nice little package with the Spa Aromatherapy scent that was included in my massage. It had a Spa face mask with beads for sleep or relaxation and a sample of the oil, lotion and body wash. So decadent and a nice lil extra sumthin. Overall the Spa was a 10/10 would recommend. So glad we took this time to truly get pampered and hope we all make sure to keep this self-care up at least quarterly.
